==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[vernaculus]]'', meaning "native" or "indigenous". The original meaning was "belonging to homeborn slaves".

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# Everyday [[speech]], including [[colloquialism]]s, as opposed to [[literary]] or [[liturgical]] language.
# Language unique to a particular [[group]] of people; [[jargon]].

